---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import ProfilePhoto from '../assets/seungwon Kim profile photo.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="Seungwon Kim — MBSE specialist at Dassault Systèmes, working where systems engineering meets AI."
	pubDate={new Date('June 14 2026')}
>
	<div class="profile">
		<Image src={ProfilePhoto} alt="Seungwon Kim" width={360} height={360} />
		<p class="name">Seungwon Kim</p>
	</div>

	<p>
		I define complex systems as models. For more than six years I have worked as an MBSE
		(Model-Based Systems Engineering) specialist at Dassault Systèmes, taking part in product
		development across a range of industries — home appliances, automotive, semiconductors, and
		Advanced Air Mobility (AAM). My work centers on designing system architectures and organizing
		development processes with the 3DEXPERIENCE platform and CATIA Magic.
	</p>

	<p>
		The work has two sides. One is defining a system as a structure: pulling together scattered
		information — from requirements through functional, logical, and physical layers — into a single
		model that makes complexity manageable. The other is bringing that approach to the customer.
		Because every industry faces a different problem, I have designed and validated proofs of concept
		tailored to each situation — from Magic Grid-based architecture design and FMEA automation to 1D
		simulation (Dymola) integration and model-based certification for the AAM sector. In other words,
		I work where deep technical practice meets solving a customer's actual problem.
	</p>

	<p>
		I believe the essence of systems engineering is turning complexity into a structure people can
		understand. And the way we handle that complexity is now changing quickly with AI — both how
		models are built and how they are explained and delivered to customers. That is why I am drawn to
		the place where AI and systems engineering meet: how AI can be brought into MBSE, and how the
		role of a systems engineer will change in an AI-driven era.
	</p>

	<p>
		I also care about sharing what I learn. I have been posting about systems engineering on YouTube,
		and this blog began for the same reason — a place to record the problems I work on and how I
		solve them, and to share them with others working through similar questions.
	</p>

	<p>
		The harder the engineering problem, the more I trust a systematic, model-based approach. This is
		where I write that thinking down.
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	.profile {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 2.5em;
	}
	.profile img {
		width: 180px;
		height: 180px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		object-fit: cover;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
	}
	.profile .name {
		margin-top: 0.8em;
		margin-bottom: 0;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
</style>
